      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a solid starting point for the core market, but doesn't that feel a bit... limited? We are looking at a global rollout, not just a European one. I'm seeing a lot of growth in markets like East Asia, the Middle East, and even certain segments in North America. \n\nWhen we look at these other regions, do you think the \"ideal consumer\" changes significantly in terms of their ethnicity or specific cultural identity, or is the luxury consumer profile basically the same everywhere?",
